# Testing comparison of functions and related error messages

```catala-metadata
declaration scope S1:
  internal f content integer depends on x content money
  output o content boolean

scope S1:
  definition f of x equals integer of x
  definition o equals f = f
```

```catala-test-cli
$ catala test-scope S1
┌─[ERROR]─
│
│  During evaluation: attempting to compare values with uncomparable types.
│
├─➤ tests/introspection/bad/functions.catala_en:10.25-26:
│    │
│ 10 │   definition o equals f = f
│    │                         ‾
└─ Testing comparison of functions and related error messages
#return code 123#
```


```catala-metadata
declaration foo content money depends on
    x content money
  equals
  x

declaration scope S2:
  output o content boolean

scope S2:
  definition o equals foo < foo
```

```catala-test-cli
$ catala test-scope S2
┌─[ERROR]─
│
│  During evaluation: attempting to compare values with uncomparable types.
│
├─➤ tests/introspection/bad/functions.catala_en:38.27-28:
│    │
│ 38 │   definition o equals foo < foo
│    │                           ‾
└─ Testing comparison of functions and related error messages
#return code 123#
```

```catala-metadata
declaration structure St:
  data f content money depends on x content money

declaration enumeration E:
  -- A
  -- F content St

declaration scope S3a:
  output o content boolean

declaration scope S3b:
  output o content boolean

scope S3a:
  definition o equals A = A

scope S3b:
  definition o equals F content St { -- f: foo } >= F content St { -- f: foo }
```

```catala-test-cli
$ catala test-scope S3a
┌─[RESULT]─ S3a ─
│ o = true
└─
```

```catala-test-cli
$ catala test-scope S3b
┌─[ERROR]─
│
│  During evaluation: attempting to compare values with uncomparable types.
│
├─➤ tests/introspection/bad/functions.catala_en:73.50-52:
│    │
│ 73 │   definition o equals F content St { -- f: foo } >= F content St { -- f: foo }
│    │                                                  ‾‾
└─ Testing comparison of functions and related error messages
#return code 123#
```
